 5. Session Workflow Enhancement

 The Problem: Sessions are basic. No prep vs post-session flow.

 The Solution: Session lifecycle with clear phases.

 Phase 1: Prep Mode
 - Pre-session checklist (customizable per campaign)
 - Import from previous session's "thoughts for next"
 - Quick NPC creation
 - Pull relevant NPCs/locations for reference

 Phase 2: During Session
 - NOT trying to replace VTT
 - Simple notes area for DM
 - Players can add notes from their phones (optional)
 - Reference panel for quick lookups

 Phase 3: Recap Mode
 - DM notes + player notes in one view
 - "Merge into Summary" via Intelligence
 - Extract timeline events
 - Update character statuses
 - "Thoughts for next session" field

 6. Visual Tools

 Interactive Maps:
 - Upload map images
 - Add pins with popups (link to locations, NPCs, encounters)
 - Layers: geographic, political, player knowledge
 - Basic fog of war (DM reveals regions)
 - Distance tool for travel estimation
 - Works for campaigns AND oneshots (if they add that detail)

 Relationship Diagrams:
 - Auto-generate from character relationships
 - Family tree view
 - Faction membership visualization
 - "Conspiracy board" mode with string connections
 - Export as image for sharing

 Enhanced Timeline:
 - Character-focused view (one character's journey)
 - Era/chapter grouping
 - Parallel storyline support
 - Future: In-game calendar dates

 7. Oneshot Restructuring

 Current Problem:
 - Editor is text-only, may be missing important sections
 - Run mode is confusing and tries to be a VTT
 - Oneshots get shared as templates - need to be complete for other DMs

 Oneshot Editor - Hybrid Approach:

 Keep text sections (flexible, fast):
 - Introduction (read-aloud)
 - Setting Notes
 - Session Plan
 - Twists & Secrets (DM-only)
 - Handouts

 Add structured entities (richer content):
 - NPCs - Full profiles (appearance, personality, motivation, stat reference)
 - Encounters - Difficulty, enemies, tactics, terrain, rewards
 - Locations - Description, features, connections
 - Maps - Interactive with pins linking to above

 Cross-referencing:
 - Session plan can reference [[NPC: Mira]] or [[Location: The Flask]]
 - Click reference â†’ shows inline detail
 - Everything included when published as template

 Present Mode (replaces confusing "Run Mode"):
 - Clean reading experience of adventure content
 - Section navigation (quick jump between scenes)
 - Checklist mode (mark scenes as done)
 - Expandable stat blocks inline
 - Collapsible notes panel
 - Optional simple timer in corner
 - REMOVED: Initiative tracker, HP management, conditions, player view sharing (use VTT for this)

 After session:
 - Save notes
 - Optionally rate the run
 - "Convert to Campaign" button (creates campaign from oneshot for Session 2+)

 8. AI Intelligence Hub

 Philosophy: AI should organize, import, suggest, summarize - never replace creativity.

 Centralized in Campaign/Character Intelligence (not scattered):

 Campaign Intelligence - Review Hub:
 After updating session notes, DM opens Intelligence to see:

