 Intelligence-Integrated Guidance

 On Session Notes page:
 - Empty state: "Session notes are the foundation. Intelligence uses them to suggest timeline events, detect new NPCs, and track plot threads."
 - After saving: "Notes saved! Open Campaign Intelligence to review suggestions."

 On Timeline page:
 - Empty state: "Add timeline events manually, or let Intelligence extract them from your session notes."

 On Characters page:
 - Empty state: "Add characters manually, or let Intelligence detect NPCs mentioned in session notes."

 On Intelligence page:
 - First visit: "Intelligence analyzes your campaign to save you time. It works best when session notes are up to date."
 - Before running: "Before running, make sure session notes are up to date for the best suggestions."
 - On cooldown: "Available in Xh. While you wait, add any new session notes or character details."

 On Import:
 - Start: "Import your character from a PDF, image, or text. Our AI will match fields automatically."
 - Processing: "Analyzing your document..."
 - Review: "Review the imported data below. You can edit anything before saving."

 Requirements

 - Nothing missed across the entire site
 - Tips must be accurate (not wrong/outdated)
 - Dismissable and not annoying
 - Remember what user has seen (stored in user_settings or local storage)
 - Guide workflows, not just individual features
 - Don't mention costs/credits in tips

 12. Enhanced Sharing & Discord

 Discord Auth for Invites:
 - Equal option alongside email
 - DM can invite via Discord username
 - Player connects Discord to Multiloop
 - Streamlined join flow

 Beautiful Share Pages:
 - Session 0 pitch: Full campaign overview
 - Active campaign: Party-appropriate view
 - Character share: Already good, minor enhancements

 Discord Embeds:
 - Rich previews when pasting links
 - "Copy for Discord" generates formatted text
 - Future: Discord bot (not in v1)

 ---
 Implementation Phases

 Phase 1: Foundation

 Campaign Dashboard:
 - New /campaigns/[id]/dashboard route
 - Widget system with drag-drop (use existing component patterns)
 - Default widgets: Next Session, Quick Actions, Recent Activity, Party
 - Dashboard as new default entry point
 - Canvas accessible from dashboard nav

 Basic Player Access:
 - campaign_members table
 - Email invite flow with magic links
 - Discord auth setup and invite option
 - Password-protected view links
 - Basic role system (owner, player, guest)

 Secrets Layer v1:
 - dm_notes field on characters, sessions, timeline_events, lore
 - Basic visibility toggle (public/DM only)

 Phase 2: Collaboration

 Full Player System:
 - Player session notes (player_session_notes table)
 - DM can add notes on behalf of players
 - Player dashboard view (My Character, Recent Sessions)
 - Permission controls per campaign

 Vault-Campaign Linking:
 - Character claiming flow
 - "Belongs to" field on campaign characters (optional)
 - Session 0 snapshot on claim/link
 - Bi-directional sync for appropriate fields
 - Drill-down character view in campaigns

 Party visibility:
 - Player visibility toggle
 - Revealed tracking with session attribution

 Phase 3: Visual Tools

 Interactive Maps:
 - Map upload with zoom/pan (Leaflet or similar)
 - Pin system with popups
 - Link pins to entities
 - Basic fog of war
 - Works for campaigns and oneshots

 Relationship Diagrams:
 - Auto-generate from character relationships
 - Family tree layout option
 - Faction visualization
 - Export as image

 Timeline Enhancements:
 - Character-focused view
 - Era/chapter grouping

 Phase 4: Content & Workflow

 Oneshot Restructuring:
 - Structured NPCs (new table, similar to campaign characters)
 - Structured Encounters (new table)
 - Structured Locations (new table)
 - Present mode (simplified clean reading view)
 - Remove VTT-like features from run mode

 Session Workflow:
 - Prep mode with checklist
 - Recap mode with merge
 - "Thoughts for next" field

 Oneshot â†’ Campaign conversion:
 - "Continue as Campaign" button
 - Copy NPCs, notes, settings

 Phase 5: Intelligence & Admin

 AI Intelligence Hub Enhancements:
 - Review queue UI in Campaign Intelligence
 - Timeline extraction suggestions
 - NPC detection from notes
 - Relationship suggestions
 - Merge player + DM notes
 - ğŸ‘/ğŸ‘ feedback on each suggestion
 - Cooldown system with timer display
 - "View Previous Suggestions" when on cooldown

 AI Admin Panel (/admin/ai-usage):
 - Usage metrics dashboard (calls by type, by user, over time)
 - Cost tracking dashboard (by model, by operation, burn rate)
 - Import funnel analytics (started â†’ parsed â†’ saved)
 - Intelligence effectiveness (acceptance rates, feedback ratios)
 - Model comparison views
 - Cooldown configuration per tier
 - Per-user usage drill-down
 - Alerts for anomalies (cost spikes, high error rates)

 AI Infrastructure:
 - ai_usage_logs table + logging middleware
 - ai_cooldowns table + enforcement
 - ai_suggestion_feedback table + UI integration
 - import_sessions table + funnel tracking
 - ai_tier_settings table + admin UI

 Phase 6: Tutorials & Polish

 Tutorials & Guidance:
 - Empty state messages across entire site
 - First-time tooltips (Intelligence, templates, sharing)
 - Contextual help icons on complex features
 - Workflow-aware guidance (not just feature tips)
 - Onboarding flows for new campaigns/characters
 - "What to do next" prompts

 Enhanced Sharing:
 - Discord-formatted copy button
 - Improved share page designs

 Final Polish:
 - Verify all guidance is accurate
 - Test all workflows end-to-end
 - Mobile optimization pass
 - Performance optimization

 ---
 Database Changes

 New Tables

 -- Campaign members (player access)
 campaign_members (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   campaign_id UUID REFERENCES campaigns,
   user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users NULL,
   email TEXT,
   discord_id TEXT,
   role TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'owner', 'co_dm', 'player', 'contributor', 'guest'
   permissions JSONB DEFAULT '{}',
   character_id UUID NULL, -- linked campaign character
   vault_character_id UUID NULL, -- linked vault character
   invite_token TEXT,
   invited_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
   joined_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
   status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending'
 )

 -- Player session notes
 player_session_notes (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   session_id UUID REFERENCES sessions,
   character_id UUID REFERENCES characters,
   added_by_user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users, -- who typed it
   attributed_to_user_id UUID NULL, -- whose perspective (null if no account)
   notes TEXT,
   source TEXT DEFAULT 'manual', -- 'manual', 'discord_import', 'player_submitted'
   is_shared_with_party BOOLEAN DEFAULT true,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
   updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- DM secrets / visibility layer
 entity_secrets (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   entity_type TEXT, -- 'character', 'session', 'timeline_event', 'lore'
   entity_id UUID,
   field_name TEXT NULL, -- null = general DM notes
   content TEXT,
   visibility TEXT DEFAULT 'dm_only', -- 'dm_only', 'party', 'public'
   revealed_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL,
   revealed_in_session_id UUID NULL,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- Map pins for interactive maps
 map_pins (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   map_id UUID, -- can reference world_maps or oneshot_maps
   map_type TEXT, -- 'campaign', 'oneshot'
   x FLOAT,
   y FLOAT,
   label TEXT,
   description TEXT,
   icon TEXT,
   color TEXT,
   linked_entity_type TEXT NULL,
   linked_entity_id UUID NULL,
   visibility TEXT DEFAULT 'public',
   sort_order INTEGER,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- Dashboard layouts
 dashboard_layouts (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
   campaign_id UUID REFERENCES campaigns,
   layout JSONB,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
   updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- Oneshot structured NPCs
 oneshot_npcs (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   oneshot_id UUID REFERENCES oneshots,
   name TEXT NOT NULL,
   description TEXT,
   appearance TEXT,
   personality TEXT,
   motivation TEXT,
   stat_block TEXT, -- formatted reference
   external_link TEXT, -- link to D&D Beyond etc.
   image_url TEXT,
   sort_order INTEGER,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- Oneshot structured encounters
 oneshot_encounters (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   oneshot_id UUID REFERENCES oneshots,
   name TEXT NOT NULL,
   description TEXT,
   difficulty TEXT, -- 'easy', 'medium', 'hard', 'deadly'
   enemies JSONB, -- [{name, count, hp, ac, notes}]
   tactics TEXT,
   terrain TEXT,
   rewards TEXT,
   map_id UUID NULL, -- link to map if applicable
   sort_order INTEGER,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- Oneshot structured locations
 oneshot_locations (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   oneshot_id UUID REFERENCES oneshots,
   name TEXT NOT NULL,
   description TEXT,
   features TEXT,
   connected_locations UUID[], -- links to other locations
   map_id UUID NULL,
   sort_order INTEGER,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- Session 0 snapshots for characters
 character_snapshots (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   vault_character_id UUID REFERENCES vault_characters,
   campaign_id UUID REFERENCES campaigns,
   snapshot_data JSONB, -- full character state at join time
   snapshot_type TEXT DEFAULT 'session_0',
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ
 )

 -- AI usage tracking
 ai_usage_logs (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
   operation_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'campaign_intelligence', 'character_intelligence', 'import', 'merge', etc.
   model_used TEXT, -- 'gemini-pro-3', 'gemini-flash-3', etc.
   input_tokens INTEGER,
   output_tokens INTEGER,
   cost_usd DECIMAL(10,6),
   duration_ms INTEGER,
   status TEXT DEFAULT 'success', -- 'success', 'error', 'cancelled'
   error_message TEXT NULL,
   -- Context
   campaign_id UUID NULL,
   character_id UUID NULL,
   oneshot_id UUID NULL,
   -- Metadata
   metadata JSONB DEFAULT '{}', -- additional context
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
 )

 -- AI cooldown tracking
 ai_cooldowns (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
   cooldown_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'campaign_intelligence', 'character_intelligence'
   entity_id UUID NULL, -- campaign_id or character_id
   last_run_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
   next_available_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
 )

 -- AI suggestion feedback
 ai_suggestion_feedback (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
   usage_log_id UUID REFERENCES ai_usage_logs, -- link to the AI run
   suggestion_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'timeline_event', 'npc_detection', 'relationship', etc.
   suggestion_content TEXT, -- the suggestion text
   action_taken TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'accepted', 'edited', 'dismissed'
   feedback TEXT NULL, -- 'positive', 'negative', NULL
   edit_details TEXT NULL, -- what they changed if edited
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
 )

 -- Import tracking (for funnel analysis)
 import_sessions (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   user_id UUID REFERENCES auth.users,
   import_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'pdf', 'image', 'text'
   target_type TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'vault_character', 'campaign_character', etc.
   status TEXT DEFAULT 'started', -- 'started', 'parsed', 'reviewed', 'saved', 'cancelled'
   usage_log_id UUID REFERENCES ai_usage_logs NULL, -- link to AI cost
   file_size_bytes INTEGER NULL,
   parse_duration_ms INTEGER NULL,
   -- Timestamps for funnel
   started_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
   parsed_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL,
   reviewed_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL, -- when user saw results
   completed_at TIMESTAMPTZ NULL, -- saved or cancelled
   created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
 )

 -- AI tier settings (admin-configurable)
 ai_tier_settings (
   id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
   tier TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE, -- 'free', 'founder', 'pro'
   campaign_intelligence_cooldown_hours INTEGER DEFAULT 12,
   character_intelligence_cooldown_hours INTEGER DEFAULT 12,
   import_limit_per_day INTEGER NULL, -- NULL = unlimited
   updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
   updated_by UUID REFERENCES auth.users
 )

 Existing Table Modifications

 -- campaigns: add collaboration settings
 ALTER TABLE campaigns ADD COLUMN collaboration_settings JSONB DEFAULT '{}';

 -- characters: add visibility and ownership
 ALTER TABLE characters ADD COLUMN dm_notes TEXT;
 ALTER TABLE characters ADD COLUMN visibility TEXT DEFAULT 'public';
 ALTER TABLE characters ADD COLUMN vault_character_id UUID NULL;
 ALTER TABLE characters ADD COLUMN controlled_by_user_id UUID NULL;
 ALTER TABLE characters ADD COLUMN controlled_by_email TEXT NULL;
 ALTER TABLE characters ADD COLUMN controlled_by_discord TEXT NULL;

 -- vault_characters: add campaign tracking
 ALTER TABLE vault_characters ADD COLUMN campaign_links JSONB DEFAULT '[]';
 -- [{campaign_id, character_id, joined_at, snapshot_id}]

 -- sessions: add workflow fields
 ALTER TABLE sessions ADD COLUMN phase TEXT DEFAULT 'planned';
 ALTER TABLE sessions ADD COLUMN prep_checklist JSONB DEFAULT '[]';
 ALTER TABLE sessions ADD COLUMN thoughts_for_next TEXT;

 -- timeline_events, lore entries: add dm_notes
 ALTER TABLE timeline_events ADD COLUMN dm_notes TEXT;
 ALTER TABLE timeline_events ADD COLUMN visibility TEXT DEFAULT 'public';
 -- (similar for lore tables)

 -- oneshots: add structured content flags
 ALTER TABLE oneshots ADD COLUMN has_structured_npcs BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;
 ALTER TABLE oneshots ADD COLUMN has_structured_encounters BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;
 ALTER TABLE oneshots ADD COLUMN has_structured_locations BOOLEAN DEFAULT false;

 ---
 Key User Flows

 Flow 1: DM Invites Player

 DM: Campaign â†’ Settings â†’ Members â†’ "Invite Player"
 â†“
 Choose: Email OR Discord
 â†“
 Optionally assign to existing character: "This is for Thornwick"
 â†“
 Player receives invite (email or Discord DM)
 â†“
 Player clicks link â†’ Join page
 â†“
 If has account: Link vault character OR claim assigned character
 If no account: Create account OR view as contributor
 â†“
 Player appears in member list
 â†“
 DM can adjust permissions anytime

 Flow 2: Player Claims Character

 DM created "Thornwick" and set "Belongs to: player@email.com"
 â†“
 Player creates account with player@email.com
 â†“
 Player joins campaign
 â†“
 Sees: "Thornwick was created for you. Claim to your vault?"
 â†“
 Player clicks "Claim"
 â†“
 Prompt: "Want to add more details?"
   - Import character sheet (PDF) â†’ AI populates
   - Add manually
   - Keep simple for now
 â†“
 Vault character created, linked to campaign character
 â†“
 Session 0 snapshot saved
 â†“
 Player now has full vault features

 Flow 3: Player Adds Session Notes

 After session, player opens campaign on phone
 â†“
 Dashboard shows "Session 12 just happened"
 â†“
 Clicks "Add My Notes"
 â†“
 Writes from their character's perspective
 â†“
 Submits
 â†“
 DM sees in session: "Thornwick's player added notes"
 â†“
 DM opens Campaign Intelligence
 â†“
 Sees suggestion: "Merge player notes into summary?"
 â†“
 Reviews, accepts with edits
 â†“
 Unified recap created

 Flow 4: DM Reveals Secret

 DM has NPC with DM note: "Actually a spy for BBEG"
 â†“
 Players discover during Session 15 (at the table, verbally)
 â†“
 After session, DM opens NPC in Multiloop
 â†“
 Clicks "Reveal" on the secret
 â†“
 Selects "Revealed in Session 15"
 â†“
 Secret now visible when players browse
 â†“
 Timeline event auto-created: "The spy was unmasked"

 ---
 Migration Safety

 Principle: Additive changes only. Zero data loss.

 For existing campaigns:
 - All existing data untouched
 - New campaign_members table starts with owner only
 - New collaboration_settings defaults to restrictive (opt-in)
 - New dm_notes fields are NULL (optional)
 - Existing campaigns work exactly as before

 For existing characters:
 - No changes to vault_characters schema (only additions)
 - New linking fields are NULL by default
 - Standalone vault use unaffected

 For wife's campaigns specifically:
 - Run migration on test copy first
 - Verify all sessions, characters, timeline, lore intact
 - Verify canvas layout preserved
 - Test all existing functionality before enabling new features

 ---
 Verification Plan

 Core Features

 1. Migration test: Run on copy of production, verify zero data loss
 2. Existing functionality: All current features work unchanged
 3. Player invite flow: Email + Discord, both paths
 4. Character claiming: Full flow with PDF import
 5. Session notes: Player adds, DM sees, merge works
 6. Secrets: Create, reveal, verify visibility
 7. Dashboard: Customize, reload, verify persistence
 8. Maps: Upload, add pins, link entities
 9. Oneshot present mode: Clean reading, no VTT features
 10. Mobile: All flows work on mobile

 AI System

 11. Intelligence suggestions: Appear correctly, categorized by type
 12. Suggestion feedback: ğŸ‘/ğŸ‘ buttons work, data saved
 13. Accept/edit/dismiss: All three actions work correctly
 14. Cooldown system: Timer shows, enforced correctly, respects tier settings
 15. Previous suggestions: Viewable when on cooldown

 AI Admin Panel

 16. Usage dashboard: Shows calls by type, by user, over time
 17. Cost tracking: Accurate cost per operation, totals correct
 18. Import funnel: Tracks started â†’ parsed â†’ saved correctly
 19. Effectiveness metrics: Acceptance rates calculated correctly
 20. Model comparison: Shows side-by-side metrics
 21. Cooldown config: Admin can edit per tier, changes apply immediately
 22. Per-user view: Can drill into individual user usage
 23. Alerts: Trigger correctly for cost spikes, anomalies

 Tutorials & Guidance

 24. Empty states: Show on all relevant pages, guide to Intelligence
 25. First-time tooltips: Show once, don't repeat
 26. Workflow guidance: Tips reference full workflow, not just features
 27. Dismissable: All tips can be dismissed
 28. Persistence: Dismissed tips stay dismissed across sessions

